Raab quits over 'flawed' Brexit agreement
The provisional agreement sets out commitments over citizens' rights after Brexit, the proposed 21-month transition period, the Â£39bn "divorce bill" and, most controversially, the "backstop" to avoid a hard border between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland.It still needs to get the stamp of approval from MPs in Parliament, and finally from the 27 other EU member states.
